abstract: It has been 3 1/2 years since Paul and Wendi M. Gilbert moved from New York City to San Francisco. But after helping prepare a dinner this Thanksgiving for the homeless in nearby Santa Cruz, Calif., they could not stop thinking about the legions of poor and homeless in the city they left behind.   "Even though we no longer live in Manhattan, we will always feel connected to The City," the Gilberts wrote recently in a letter accompanying their $25 donation to The New York Times Neediest Cases Fund. "New York often gets a bad rap about being such a cold, uncaring place, but we choose to remember the basic 'can do' spirit that has always helped New York and New Yorkers survive."
